observations.recommendation:
We recommended to the Municipal Mayor to:

Require the Municipal Accountant to determine the cost of the road lot and recognize it as part of the road network component including the cost of constructing the drainage and slope protection and other miscellaneous structure, if there is any.

Require the Municipal Accountant to periodically assess the local roads whether there is any indication that a component of the local road may be impaired and recognize an Impairment Loss to be presented as a contra-asset account.

 Cause the creation of an Inventory Committee and require the Committee to conduct an inventory of all the local roads under its jurisdiction, prepare and submit a verified Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System (RPCRNS);

Direct the General Services Officer, Municipal Engineer and Municipal Accountant to reconcile their respective records;

Require the Municipal Accountant to maintain and update subsidiary ledgers. and disclose in the notes to financial statements the local road network system as prescribed by regulation.

