observations.recommendation:
We recommended to the Municipal Mayor to direct the Municipal Accountant to:
Exhaust all means of locating the source documents of all receivables accounts such as (a) approved loan application of the livelihood program especially those with unpaid loan balances and (b) subsidiary ledger of the individual person who  availed of the loan especially those with unpaid loan balances;

Send demand letters to the debtors for the immediate settlement of receivables with the signature of the Mayor;

Request authority from the COA for the write off of dormant Due From LGU, Due from Officers and Employees, Due from NGO and Other Receivable accounts in accordance with COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016, if warranted, duly supported by a quarterly aging of dormant receivable and other relevant documents;

Draw correcting entries in the books of accounts to correct the understatement of Loans Receivable-Others Account by P20,014.89, overstatement of Due from LGU account by P286,419.72 and understatement of Other Receivable account by P11,431.53. 

We further recommended to the Municipal Mayor to cause the execution of Loan Agreement for every loans availed of by various recipients under the Municipality’s Livelihood Programs, stipulating the specific terms, conditions and penalties in case of non-payments

