observations.recommendation:
We recommended to the Municipal Mayor to:

Cause the creation of policies and guidelines to address the issue on the necessity and propriety of hiring JO workers taking into consideration the existing regular employees; 

Limit the hiring of personnel under Job Order contracts to those extremely necessary and within the age limit, and deploy only to offices that actually are in need of their services; 

Direct the Human Resource Officer to require Job Order workers to submit primary personal identification, undergo interview and evaluate the performance of each to give assurance that those hired have the skills required by the office;

Direct the Human Resource Officer to incorporate in the contract the number of man hours, quantity and duration of the work to be performed by the JO worker and require them to submit quantified accomplishment reports to support payment of wages;

Cause the reduction of number of job-order workers to accommodate the increase of daily rate pursuant to the minimum wage required under Wage Oder No. RB VIII-21.

